ers students staff and friends from us and china will make daily visits to underserved schools in and around beijing xi an ningshan and the western province of qinhai reap will meet with school administrators teachers students and their families and local officials to assess progress of its ongoing research projects in chinese migrant and rural schools click here to follow the trip blog 2009 summer fresh migrant school teacher training program migrant school teachers in china are not generally well trained summer fresh is an english training course sponsored by reap that was offered to teachers from dozens of beijing area migrant schools reap aimed to assess the impact the course on the english competency of migrant students over a six month period these are the stories of several training program participants and program volunteers read more 2009 reap deerfield xi an gaoxin research service trip six high school students from deerfield academy massachusetts united states and xian gaoxin no 1 high school xian shaanxi province china explored pressing education issues in china during june of 2009 the students sought to further understand the complexity of challenges and identify key issues in order to propose feasible options for how to better rural education under the constraints of a limited budget with funds from deerfield academy matched by reap read more stanford pku volunteer migrant school teaching program in a new service learning program organized by reap stanford and peking university students teamed up to teach english classes to several poor migrant schools around beijing as the volunteer teachers got a glimpse of the unseen beijing they learned as much as the migrant children they were teaching in addition to establishing the program reap also conducted a thorough program evaluation survey to analyze the effectiveness of the program read more reap internship program reap also makes an effort to host high school and college interns both in our beijing and stanford offices to work on our research and development efforts this program serves to give high school and college students hands on experience researching education issues in rural china several of reap's interns have reported the experience to be meaningful and life altering reap also benefits from the labor of capable students read more stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
